00:59:10,496 --> 00:59:17,420
Rym: They add a stealth element that I have not encountered in Metroid games I've played before.

757
00:59:17,942 --> 00:59:20,512
Rym: Metroid Fusion has the, I never played Metroid Fusion.

758
00:59:20,532 --> 00:59:21,215
Rym: full disclosure.

759
00:59:21,919 --> 00:59:22,381
Scott: A little bit.

760
00:59:22,461 --> 00:59:22,742
Scott: Yeah.

761
00:59:22,823 --> 00:59:24,872
Scott: Well then how do you understand what's going on in Metroid Dread?

762
00:59:25,234 --> 00:59:28,710
Rym: Uh, cause the plot is really simplistic and it's really straightforward.

763
00:59:29,912 --> 00:59:37,337
Scott: Well, you know, anyway, so yeah, the Emmy thing is basically there are certain zones in each, in each of the areas of the planet.

764
00:59:37,598 --> 00:59:43,681
Scott: Cause it's a Metroid game, named areas of the planet, but each major named area has a zone.

765
00:59:43,962 --> 00:59:45,327
Scott: That's like the Emmy zone.

766
00:59:45,347 --> 00:59:54,241
Scott: So when you go there, there's like these doors and you can just tell it cause it signals to you visually that once you go in that door, you'll be in the Emmy zone.

767
00:59:54,282 --> 00:59:56,010
Scott: And the Emmy zone is all weird and scary.

768
00:59:56,090 --> 00:59:59,803
Scott: And there's an Emmy in there and you basically can't kill it.

769
01:00:00,023 --> 01:00:00,746
Scott: It's invincible.

770
01:00:01,087 --> 01:00:05,043
Scott: If it grabs you, you can escape with some really well-timed button presses.

771
01:00:05,164 --> 01:00:06,470
Scott: Maybe if you're really good.

772
01:00:07,130 --> 01:00:11,406
Rym: The game is even like, look, listen, kids, don't think this is a mechanic.

773
01:00:11,446 --> 01:00:14,035
Rym: We expect you to use, do not rely on this.

774
01:00:14,075 --> 01:00:15,622
Rym: Do not like try to get good at it.

775
01:00:15,903 --> 01:00:17,128
Rym: It is not the way to play.

776
01:00:17,168 --> 01:00:18,853
Scott: I'm sure there are people who can do it every time.

777
01:00:18,893 --> 01:00:19,454
Scott: No problem.

778
01:00:19,575 --> 01:00:21,800
Scott: I had about like a 30% success rate.

779
01:00:21,820 --> 01:00:26,492
Scott: I'm getting fascinating.

780
01:00:27,054 --> 01:00:31,107
Rym: Uh, it as echoes of something that five nights at Freddy's did very well too.

781
01:00:31,127 --> 01:00:38,857
Rym: Uh, if the game was, cause the way this works is when you get into an Emmy zone, they will like, listen for you, hunt you down.

782
01:00:38,897 --> 01:00:42,731
Rym: And if they touch you barring this quick time event, it's instant death.

783
01:00:42,792 --> 01:00:43,315
Rym: You just die.

784
01:00:43,415 --> 01:00:44,300
Rym: There's nothing you can do.

785
01:00:44,340 --> 01:00:45,125
Rym: You cannot fight them.

786
01:00:45,165 --> 01:00:46,552
Rym: You cannot even like shooting them.

787
01:00:46,592 --> 01:00:47,636
Rym: Doesn't really do anything.

788
01:00:47,957 --> 01:00:49,363
Scott: You just, they're just invincible.

789
01:00:49,825 --> 01:00:55,546
Rym: So if they, if them touching you was just instant death, that's still really scary.

790
01:00:56,027 --> 01:01:11,122
Rym: But the fact that there's this tiny chance you might be able to escape by hitting X at the right time during that animation gives you this false sense of hope and makes you like engage more with this instant death mechanic and it increases.

791
01:01:11,202 --> 01:01:17,112
Scott: Otherwise, if you didn't have a chance, you would just like, you know, you know, as soon as you knew you were caught, you'd be like, fuck it.

792
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:17,293
Scott: Right.

793
01:01:17,313 --> 01:01:22,397
Scott: You wouldn't even, but it's like you hold on and you actually experience the horror of being caught.

794
01:01:22,979 --> 01:01:24,184
Scott: You submit yourself to that.

795
01:01:24,304 --> 01:01:32,314
Rym: Similar to how five nights at Freddy's to escape gives you all these, it does all these things to convince you as a player, instead of just closing your eyes.

796
01:01:32,374 --> 01:01:42,353
Rym: Cause you know, the jump stairs coming, leaning in and paying attention to, so you end up getting more gotten by the jump scare than you as an intelligence adult would have been.

797
01:01:42,674 --> 01:01:49,194
Rym: This mechanic in Metroid Dread literally increases the dread you as a player feel around these Emmys.

798
01:01:49,936 --> 01:01:56,835
Rym: And I think that is the most interesting mechanical innovation used in this game, like full stop.

799
01:01:56,956 --> 01:02:02,438
Scott: Now, the problem is, is that, you know, when I started playing the game, the first couple Emmy zones, right.

800
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:03,944
Scott: It totally worked, right.

801
01:02:04,004 --> 01:02:06,133
Scott: It was very scary to go in the Emmy zones.

802
01:02:06,374 --> 01:02:08,081
Scott: The Emmy was catching me all the time.

803
01:02:08,162 --> 01:02:08,362
Scott: Right.

804
01:02:08,704 --> 01:02:14,348
Scott: But then by the third or fourth Emmy zone, I realized like, wait a minute, this game is structured in such a way.

805
01:02:14,368 --> 01:02:15,974
Scott: Like, I don't need to go.

806
01:02:16,014 --> 01:02:20,755
Scott: Cause I was trying to explore the Emmy zone while avoiding the Emmy to figure out what the hell to do in there.

807
01:02:21,237 --> 01:02:31,372
Scott: But then I realized, wait a minute, every time you encounter a new Emmy door, the game is designed for you to just run through to the next Emmy door and escape the zone.

808
01:02:31,914 --> 01:02:44,601
Scott: And if you just keep going forward in that fashion, as quickly as you can, you'll eventually arrive at the method to get rid of the Emmy permanently, then unlock that zone, removing the Emmy so that you can explore it freely.

809
01:02:44,842 --> 01:02:46,490
Scott: There's no reason to hang around in there.

810
01:02:46,750 --> 01:02:52,491
Scott: So once I realized that after the, like the third Emmy zone, I never got caught by an Emmy again, ever.

811
01:02:52,552 --> 01:03:00,827
Scott: I fucked up some platforming, like that happens sometimes, but yeah, but it's like, I just, I saw an Emmy zone and I didn't even give a shit about what was in that zone.

812
01:03:00,867 --> 01:03:02,857
Scott: I just ran from, I looked at the map.

813
01:03:02,957 --> 01:03:04,545
Scott: I said, okay, well, this is the entrance.

814
01:03:04,566 --> 01:03:05,430
Scott: Where's the next exit.

815
01:03:05,832 --> 01:03:06,996
Scott: It's probably around there.

816
01:03:07,358 --> 01:03:09,748
Scott: And I just went in, I ran through as quickly as I could.

817
01:03:09,768 --> 01:03:11,915
Scott: I didn't do stealth metal gear style.

818
01:03:12,337 --> 01:03:13,942
Scott: I didn't try to do any shenanigans.

819
01:03:14,344 --> 01:03:15,287
Scott: I just ran through.

820
01:03:15,307 --> 01:03:22,029
Scott: no exploring, no nothing, you know, got out the other side and that the Emmy was now not scary at all.

821
01:03:22,149 --> 01:03:29,015
Rym: Once I realized, you know what the deal was, I think they should not have given you, they should not have let you destroy the Emmys.

822
01:03:29,056 --> 01:03:30,161
Rym: They should have done that differently.

823
01:03:30,181 --> 01:03:31,287
Rym: I'd rather know.

824
01:03:31,387 --> 01:03:33,256
Scott: I think letting you destroy them is fine.

825
01:03:33,437 --> 01:03:41,826
Scott: I think what they should have done is given you some incentive or reason to explore and hang out in the Emmy zone while the Emmy was still there.

826
01:03:42,007 --> 01:03:42,288
Rym: Yeah.

827
01:03:42,970 --> 01:03:43,130
Scott: Right.

828
01:03:43,290 --> 01:03:47,749
Scott: Don't just construct it in such a way that like, yeah, just run through and explore it later.

829
01:03:47,829 --> 01:03:49,395
Scott: It's like, it's a Metroid game.

830
01:03:49,475 --> 01:03:51,523
Scott: I should basically always want to explore.

831
01:03:52,205 --> 01:03:54,956
Scott: And you know, this thing should basically be like, yeah.

832
01:03:54,976 --> 01:03:58,510
Rym: Imagine if it was more like the Emmy was exploring under pressure.

833
01:03:58,831 --> 01:03:59,133
Scott: Imagine

834
01:03:59,173 --> 01:04:18,067
Rym: a bigger Emmy zone that was like really vertical, let's say, and there's a bunch of shit to explore and you couldn't destroy that Emmy, but it was further away from you and you had like more room to maneuver and you couldn't, you just literally had to, with that sense of dread play Metroid in a place where there's only one monster and it's really, really dangerous.

835
01:04:18,568 --> 01:04:21,359
Scott: But yeah, and also despite being stealth, right?

836
01:04:21,399 --> 01:04:24,371
Scott: You know, the old, the old palace guard stealth game, right?

837
01:04:24,653 --> 01:04:27,084
Scott: You're hiding in the hedge maze, Zelda 64 style.

838
01:04:27,144 --> 01:04:28,370
Scott: There's a lot of other games that do that.

839
01:04:29,572 --> 01:04:30,758
Scott: it's like, they could have done that.

840
01:04:30,798 --> 01:04:43,873
Scott: You could have brought in more than one Emmy and been like, okay, you're in a ball in some vents and it's like, go through the vents with the correct timing, looking at where the Emmys are so that their flashlights don't touch you while you're in ball shape.

841
01:04:44,215 --> 01:04:47,248
Rym: They made all the Emmys the same, which was also kind of boring.

842
01:04:47,288 --> 01:04:49,357
Rym: Like I wish the Emmys, they're not all exactly the same.

843
01:04:49,397 --> 01:04:55,761
Scott: They do get more dangerous, but dealing with them is effectively the same because you just don't run away from them.

844
01:04:55,782 --> 01:04:56,885
Scott: It's a problem.

845
01:04:56,925 --> 01:05:02,564
Rym: I call it the portal problem back when we played portal two all the way to the end.

846
01:05:02,886 --> 01:05:06,704
Rym: When I realized that portal one and portal two, the puzzles are really good.

847
01:05:06,724 --> 01:05:07,529
Rym: I really love those games.

848
01:05:07,569 --> 01:05:10,464
Rym: In fact, I'm actually finally playing the multiplayer with our friend right now.

849
01:05:10,766 --> 01:05:12,212
Rym: We're going to finish that like tomorrow.

850
01:05:12,994 --> 01:05:15,261
Scott: It's really early 20 years too late, but it's fun.

851
01:05:15,782 --> 01:05:36,112
Rym: But I realized like portal two got really easy when in the course of my playthrough pretty early on, I realized that there's so few avenues of solving puzzles just with the limited tools you have in the game that you can kind of just fall forward into solutions without thinking about the problem at all.

852
01:05:36,433 --> 01:05:38,862
Rym: Like, oh, there's two angled places.

853
01:05:39,184 --> 01:05:40,810
Rym: Definitely going to make something momentum.

854
01:05:40,951 --> 01:05:42,417
Rym: shoot out of those angles.

855
01:05:42,839 --> 01:05:53,375
Rym: One of the two of them will get me to the next area or we'll get the cube to the next area and approaching from the every puzzle in portal two with like one or two eventually rare exceptions.

856
01:05:53,958 --> 01:05:57,955
Rym: You can just fall forward into victory without even understanding what the puzzle was.

857
01:05:58,377 --> 01:05:59,985
Rym: And I've noticed the Emmys were the same way.

858
01:06:00,226 --> 01:06:05,185
Rym: Just fucking run and you'll beat the Emmy eventually without having to think about it at all.

859
01:06:06,209 --> 01:06:13,818
Scott: And I just think that puzzles though, there is one mini puzzle and that is, you know, you, you have in each Emmy area, you eventually beat.

860
01:06:13,838 --> 01:06:21,590
Scott: this brain thing is reminiscent of the original mother brain and you get your weapon temporarily powered up in such a way that it can defeat the Emmy.

861
01:06:21,730 --> 01:06:28,375
Rym: I like how you have to do the really like scary thing of shoot at it while it's approaching you until you melt the cover.

862
01:06:28,876 --> 01:06:34,556
Scott: But it's that sequence is actually sort of a puzzle because you need to shoot the gun at the Emmy.

863
01:06:34,957 --> 01:06:40,743
Scott: You need to charge it up, shoot it at the Emmy for a long enough period of time for it to break through the Emmy, right?

864
01:06:40,924 --> 01:06:42,350
Scott: It's not just like shoot it and you beat it.

865
01:06:42,832 --> 01:07:01,325
Scott: So it's a mini puzzle of you have to get Samus into a position where the Emmy is far enough away and coming at you slowly face first so that you can now get the weapon ready and fire it and have enough time to kill the Emmy with it before the Emmy reaches Samus.

866
01:07:01,826 --> 01:07:08,409
Scott: And it's like a mini puzzle to examine, you know, the limited arena in which the Emmy is and where you can go.

867
01:07:08,429 --> 01:07:11,484
Rym: Is there a really long one time it got me, there's a really long place.

868
01:07:11,524 --> 01:07:12,489
Rym: I think it was the third Emmy.

869
01:07:12,509 --> 01:07:13,996
Rym: And I was like, okay, I'll do the obvious thing.

870
01:07:14,036 --> 01:07:16,527
Rym: I'll stand at the end of this long, long area.

871
01:07:16,547 --> 01:07:18,174
Rym: And then I have a long time to shoot it.

872
01:07:18,736 --> 01:07:21,507
Rym: And it didn't follow down where I expected right away.

873
01:07:21,849 --> 01:07:25,662
Rym: And for just a second, I think, oh, did it go in and it fell on top of me.

874
01:07:26,505 --> 01:07:26,766
Scott: Yep.

875
01:07:27,047 --> 01:07:32,591
Scott: It's, there's a little mini puzzle of how do you get, you got to get the Emmy into the right spot and Samus into the right spot.

876
01:07:32,853 --> 01:07:45,539
Scott: And then, you know, there's an action game element of not only to do that, you have to skillfully get the weapon out and start shooting it with good aim and keep that good aim right on Emmy's head until it's destroyed without fucking up.

877
01:07:46,502 --> 01:07:50,456
Scott: So it's, that's a fun little game, like a sub game within a game there.

878
01:07:50,496 --> 01:08:06,639
Rym: But aesthetically, the other thing, the Emmys are not that interesting of a puzzle for all the reasons we discussed, but the other cool thing about them is at least in terms of their design, they are so creepy that like burbling chirping noise that they make when they're hunting you is fantastically creepy.

879
01:08:08,103 --> 01:08:08,264
Scott: Yeah.

880
01:08:08,344 --> 01:08:13,922
Scott: Everything aesthetic about this game is 100% on point, like nothing wrong with it whatsoever.

881
01:08:13,942 --> 01:08:16,711
Rym: The environments are all radically different and interesting.

882
01:08:16,751 --> 01:08:17,593
Scott: It's very Metroidy.

883
01:08:17,953 --> 01:08:19,738
Scott: All the Metroid tropes are intact.

884
01:08:20,038 --> 01:08:22,505
Rym: Yeah.

885
01:08:23,127 --> 01:08:24,009
Rym: I'm really enjoying it.

886
01:08:25,430 --> 01:08:27,902
